title: PLYMOUTH COLLEGE UPDATE: Jason Lamb wins Liberty League honors
text: Posted Oct. 18, 2015 at 12:01 AM Posted Oct. 18, 2015 at 12:01 AM WPI linebacker and Plymouth South graduate Jason Lamb has been selected the Liberty League Football Defensive Performer of the Week. He was also named to the D3football.com Team of the Week. Lamb stuffed the stats in WPI's 29-21 road victory at Union. The junior outside linebacker recorded a three-yard tackle-for-loss that was a critical safety and hauled an interception on Union's final drive with 53 seconds remaining. Lamb also chipped in with a nine-yard sack, a pass break-up and a recovered fumble to go along with four total tackles. Wicked Local
